Reach the 15th wave of a pumpkin moon, where evil lurks among the autumn harvest.
Smash a demon or crimson altar with a powerful, holy hammer.
Slay the Insane Cultist, a mad magician with powerful spells.
Unlock one of the dungeon's large, mysterious chests with a special key.
Survive a blood moon, a nocturnal event where the rivers run red and monsters swarm aplenty.
Defeat Skeletron, the cursed guardian of the dungeon.
Defeat the three nocturnal mechanical menaces: the Twins, the Destroyer, and Skeletron Prime.
Defeat the Flying Dutchman, the sails of the plunderin' skies.
Defeat the Dreadnautilus, murderous mollusk lurking beneath the surface of the sanguine seas.
Defeat the Empress of Light, responsible for all those flashy lights and glitter.
Repel the strongest forces the Old One's Army can muster.
Defeat Queen Slime, giving the coup-de-grace to the sovereign of all that jiggles.
You were so preoccupied with whether or not you could open the chest that you didn't stop to think if you should.
Triumph over the frost legion, a festive family of maniacal snowman mobsters.
Do You Want to Slay a Snowman?
Craft a drax or pickaxe axe using hallowed bars, and the souls of the three mechanical bosses.
Steal a key from the dungeon's undead denizens, and unlock one of their precious golden chests.
Equip a dye in every possible dye slot.
Mine a powerful ore that has been newly blessed upon your world.
Defeat the Eye of Cthulhu, an ocular menace who only appears at night.
Equip armor or vanity clothing in all three social slots.

Defeat Duke Fishron, mutant terror of the sea.
Fly a kite on a windy day.
Enter a misty graveyard filled with the surly dead.

Build or encounter a glowing mushroom field above the surface.
Defeat every type of slime there is!
Consume a life fruit, which grows in the thick of subterranean jungle grass.
Obtain the Terraspark Boots, forged from the finest boots of fire and ice.
Obtain the Zenith, the culmination of a journey forged into the ultimate sword.
Drop a lure in a pool of lava for a pre-fried haul!
Triumph over a goblin invasion, a ragtag regiment of crude, barbaric, pointy-eared warriors and their shadowflame sorcerers.
Complete your 10th quest for the angler.
Discover and smash your first heart crystal underground.
Obtain an anvil made from iron or lead.
Defeat a Goblin Summoner, conjurers of the darkest flames.
Discover a golden chest underground and take a peek at its contents.
Reach the 15th wave of a frost moon, where the festive season quickly degrades into madness.
Defeat a Mothership, overminds of the martian invaders.
You can only go down from here!
Build a house in a mushroom biome and have the Truffle move in.
Spelunk deep enough to reach the molten underworld.
Unleash the ancient spirits of light and darkness across your world, enabling much stronger foes and showering the world with dazzling treasures (and rainbows!).
Stumble into a spider cavern in the underground.
Survive a solar eclipse, a day darker than night filled with creatures of horror.
Defeat Golem, the stone-faced ritualistic idol of the lihzahrd tribe.

Travel a total of 26.2 miles on foot.
Defeat the Brain of Cthulhu, an enormous demon brain which haunts the creeping crimson.
Equip armor in all three armor slots: head, chest, and feet.
Do battle against the Twins, the Destroyer, and Skeletron Prime simultaneously and emerge victorious.
Craft a molten pickaxe using the hottest of materials.
Build a house suitable enough for your first town NPC, such as the guide, to move into.
Fire a Bee Gun while wearing a full set of Bee Armor.
Defeat the Ancient Cultist, fanatical leader of the dungeon coven.
Obtain your first hammer via crafting or otherwise.
Mine your first nugget of ore with a pickaxe.
Deliver headpats to the town pet.
Mine chlorophyte, an organic ore found deep among the thickest of flora.
Defeat the Pumpking, the spooky lord of hallow's eve.
Fire a rainbow gun while riding on a unicorn.
Have all possible town NPCs living in your world.
Obtain a rare treasure from a difficult monster in the dungeon.

Defeat King Slime, the lord of all things slimy.

Defeat the four celestial towers of the moon.
Craft a mana crystal out of fallen stars, and consume it.
Survive the slime rain, where gelatinous organisms fall from the sky in droves.
Defeat the Wall of Flesh, the master and core of the world who arises after a great, burning sacrifice.
Defeat the Queen Bee, the matriarch of the jungle hives.
Complete a grand total of 200 quests for the angler.
Obtain a Terra Blade, forged from the finest blades of light and darkness.
Meet with a tenant who's as happy as they possibly can be!
Breach the impenetrable walls of the jungle temple.
Defeat Plantera, the overgrown monstrosity of the jungle's depths.
There are Some Who Call Him...
What you're celebrating doesn't matter, just throw a party already!
Triumph over a martian invasion, when beings from out of this world come to scramble your brains and probe you in uncomfortable places.

Complete your 25th quest for the angler.
Trick a gnome into turning into stone!
Defeat an enemy by running it over with a minecart.

How come {Bartender} won't sell me any ale? I want to try some! What a grouch!
I don't have a mommy or a daddy, but I have a lot of fish! It's close enough!
Whaaaat?! Can't you see I'm winding up fishing line??
I have enough fish! I don't need your help right now!
There's no chefs in all of {WorldName}, so I have to cook all this fish myself!
Hey! Watch it! I'm setting up traps for my biggest prank ever! No one will see it coming! Don't you dare tell anyone!
Let a kid give you some advice, never touch your tongue to an ice block! Wait, forget what I said, I totally want to see you do it!
Ever heard of a barking fish?! I haven't, I'm just wondering if you did!
{WorldName} is filled to the brim with the most outlandish kinds of fish!
I'm bummed out! There's probably been fish that have gone extinct before I even was born, and that's not fair!
Wooow! You've bothered me, like, {AnglerCompletedQuestsCount} times! If I didn't have a cool fish for each time, I would be really mad!
Did you know I have {AnglerCompletedQuestsCount} amazingly awesome fish now!? That's because as far as errand monkeys go, you're actually a bit useful!
I don't have anything for you to do right now.
You have entertained me enough for today, go.
You are done, the grand {Angler} dismisses you!
Only one fish a day, please go away!
I haven't even used the last fish you gave me.  I don't need another.

I found this spectacular place draped in giant glowing mushrooms! Everything was blue! I was picking some of the mushrooms I found next to a glistening blue lake, when one of the mushrooms snapped at me and swam away! I want to give it a taste of its own medicine, and give it a good chompin'! What I mean is, you gotta get it for me!

(Caught in Glowing Mushroom Fields)

Did you know there's magical islands that float up high in the sky? Bet you didn't! They say angels live in the sky, and I believe those angels have fins and gills and swim around! I believe you must catch one for me!

(Caught in Sky Lakes)

Na na na na na na na Bat-FISH! That means go digging underground, fetch it, and bring it to me!

(Caught in Underground & Caverns)

Ow! Don't get near me! I got stung by a Bloody Man-O-War! In case you're not smart enough to know what that is, it's the most menacing jellyfish in all of {WorldName}! Go to that rotten crimson and catch it if you dare! 

(Caught in Crimson)

Normally I could care less if I see fishbones floating in the water underground, but this one was swimming! What, you thought that only human skeletons still flailed about in {WorldName}? Get it for me so I can stick it in someone's bed!

(Caught in Underground & Caverns)

The subterranean jungles of {WorldName} have the weirdest things! Like, there's this fish I saw that looked just like a giant bumblebee! I'm allergic to bees, so you have to catch it for me! I bet it'd taste like a tuna and honey sandwich!

(Caught in Honey)

Out in the forest, I was fishing right? Well guess what! A bunny hopped up to me! Then another one hopped up, and another... suddenly I'm surrounded by bunnies! One even swam up to me from the water, but it had no legs! I fell outta my chair in surprise and all the bunnies scurried off! I want that bunny fish as a pet, so you better catch it for me! Pronto!

(Caught in Surface)

Yarr matey! Shiver me timbers! Avast, scallywags! There's a pirate captain who once had a pet fish named Cap'n Tunabeard, but during a big storm the fishbowl fell overboard! It has a hook for a tail, and an eyepatch and everything! You need to fetch me that fish, so I can be as cool as a pirate! Obviously it's out in the ocean somewhere! Duh!

(Caught in Ocean)

I finally found a jungle cat that likes water! I think it's because it's also part fish. I don't know why this happened, and I don't want to know. I just want it in my hands, and make it snappy!

(Caught in Jungle Surface)

There's a rumor going around that there are islands that float high up in the sky, and that they have amazing treasure! Who cares about that though, what's even cooler is that sometimes lakes form in the clouds, and in those lakes are fish made out of clouds! I wanna know what it tastes like, so you better go catch it for me!

(Caught in Sky Lakes)

I saw this bright orange and colorful fish by the ocean, and it was looking around frantically as though it was seeking a lost family member! Go catch it for me, so that another one will show up looking frantically for him instead!

(Caught in Ocean)

There's a cursed fish swimming in the waters of the deepest corruption! It was forged of the cursed flames that spread from the fallen horrors that lurk down there. They say not even water can put out this fire, and that it can burn forever. I can think of some awesome things I can do with a fish like that! You gonna go get it for me, or are you too chicken!?

(Caught in Corruption)

I hear in the underworld, that the King of all demons is actually a fish! Just imagine the absolute power I would have if you caught it for me!

(Caught in Caverns)

Those Derplings in the jungle are the most scary creatures I've ever seen! Good thing is, sometimes they don't have legs! These ones live in the water and are a lot less scary! Catch me one now so I can see what they taste like without being scared half to death!

(Caught in Jungle Surface)

I was reeling in the big one when this funny talking zombie burst out of the forest lake and started rambling on about this 'ferocious' species of fish made out of dirt! He says it could suffocate ten blokes his size, or something like that... I want it! NOW!

(Caught in Surface & Underground)

The demolitionist was raising cane about losing a stick of dynamite in the lake out in the forest. He has like, so many, so why does one matter? Apparently, because it grew fins and started swimming away! I don't know where he gets his materials to make those things, but that one is clearly possessed! Reel it in and bring it to me, I always wanted a suicide bombing fish! Don't ask why...

(Caught in Surface)

I bet you're not brave enough to find the Eater of Plankton. A corrupt fish that was mutated from a severed piece of the Eater of Worlds itself! Capture it and bring it to me, and prove to me you're not a wuss!

(Caught in Corruption)

I love collecting those bright yellow stars that fall from the sky! I love it even more when they land on someone's head. But.. but.. nothing beats a star that falls in a foresty lake and turns into a fish! That's just totally rad, and you're just rad enough to get it for me!

(Caught in Sky Lakes)

I don't know what's worse, a bone fish or a bone fish with HANDS. This Fish-o-Tron deep in the caverns really freaks me out! I think it's possessed by the same evil spirits that possessed that old man by the dungeon! I double duck dare you to go catch it!

(Caught in Caverns)

There's a legend of a mighty being known as the Fishron! It's part pig, part dragon, and part FISH! I hear it hangs around in the frozen subterranean lakes of the coldest part of the world! I'm not going there, so YOU go catch it and makes sure it lands in my hands! I'm so excited!

(Caught in Underground Tundra)

Those demons in the underworld really like voodoo dolls, but I think there's a doll out there who was blasted with way too much magic! It turned into a fish and it does stuff on its own. I dare you to go down and get me one! I'd watch out for the boiling lava, because it burns you to death and that won't get me my fish!

(Caught in Caverns)

I was trying to sleep by the hill lakeside when this fish swooped down at me. It was flying! It also had the face of a lady and had feathers! I think I screamed louder than she did! Hey you, go make her pay for scaring me like that!

(Caught in Sky Lakes & Surface)

There's a piece of the Hunger that morphed from the Wall of Flesh into a small fish-like thing that swims around aimlessly in the underworld and it's gross and it's yucky and I want it now!

(Caught in Caverns)

Did you know deep in the crimson, some of those creatures make this gross yellow stuff? I overheard a crazy story about a pool of it having melted together into a shape of a fish and it swims around and everything! Fetch it for me, so I can stick it in someone's toilet!

(Caught in Crimson)

A really long fish that looks like a sword's sheath swims in the murky waters of the corruption! It looks a lot like ebonstone, so don't let it fool you! That's right, you. You're catching it, not me!

(Caught in Corruption)

Oooooohhh, I'm going to be SO rich! Deep in the caverns, there is a fish made out of gemstones! Don't ask me how, I don't know, all I know is that this fish is totally awesome and you're going to catch it for me!

(Caught in Underground & Caverns)

There's some interesting critters to be found in the deeper Hallows, I tell you! They glow this crazy purple color and it messes with my eyes! It's totally wild, so I want you to catch a fish like that for me!

(Caught in Underground Hallow)

Watch your step when wading through jungle waters! Why? No, not because I care about you being eaten by piranhas. I care because you'll step on one of my favorite kinds of fish, the Mud Fish! I also care a lot that you're going to grab me one as a pet!

(Caught in Jungle)

What's white and tan and fluffy and lives in a frozen underground lake? A mutant flinxfin! I wasn't telling a joke, you know, there really is a mutated variety of Flinx that is more adapted to an aquatic lifestyle! I want it to adapt to my fishbowl, so make sure that happens!

(Caught in Underground Tundra)

It's a whale! It's a dolphin! No, it's a penguin fish! Oh, and look, it's you! You get to bring me one! You do know they only like cold water, right?

(Caught in Tundra)

There's a really really rare type of pixie that's born with so many wings that it can't actually fly! It swims with the fishes in the lakes surrounded by that blue colored grass. My fish tank needs a lamp, so I want you to catch me that pixie!

(Caught in Hallow)

I read this ancient story about a fish that looks like a magical scarab! That's beetle, for simpletons like you! Where do you find it? Where do you think? In the desert, duh! Don't look at me like that... it's true! There is actually water out there! I'd go, but I don't like having my eyeballs pecked out by vultures. So... you do it!

(Caught in Desert)

I'm sure someone, a really stupid someone, tried to tell you there was no water in the desert! They were absolutely and positively wrong! There's this thing called an Oasis, and it has water in it! Guess what happens when you have water!? That's right, you have fish! Weird fish that try to sting you and pinch you and do all kinds of other mean things to you! A perfect pet for me, and a perfect job for you!

(Caught in Desert)

In the forest, the slimes are kinda gross. Slimefish are even more so! I don't want to swim with slimes, so yoink one out of the water for me!

(Caught in Surface Forest)

I saw a fish that had eight legs! Nope! Not happening! You're fishing it for me, so it's not alive when I hold it! That's the last time I go fishing so deep in the cavern!

(Caught in Underground & Caverns)

Apparently, Demon Eyes can sometimes be amphibious. They don't fly, they swim! I want to see the look on someone's face when they find it in their bathtub! They hang around the same areas. That means you reel one in for me!

(Caught in Sky Lakes & Surface)

Piranhas and sharks are ugly! Soooo ugly! Did you know there's a fish that looks very pretty and still can eat your face off? I would pay 2 platinum to see that happen, by the way... To the point, though, you catchy for me. Just make sure I have it before you lose your face!

(Caught Jungle Surface)

You ever wonder why the lakes on the surface of the snowy areas of {WorldName} never ice over? I don't. The fish, however, do! A fish made out of ice would make a great offering to the mighty and amazing {Angler}! Go, my loyal subject, and bring me this Tundra Trout with haste!

(Caught in Surface Tundra)

Unicorns and rainbows are absolutely great! They're everywhere, even in the water. No, really, I actually saw a unicorn fish in the Hallowed lake! Your job is to reel it up and let me have it as a pet!

(Caught in Hallow)

I know something youuuuu don't! Fine, I'll tell you, there's a terrifying creature that flies among the stars! I'm not making this up! It's called a Wyvern! But, but, you knew that already, right? Well what you don't know is that they are born and raised as tadpoles! So, they're actually like.. well, a frog! Hop to it and get me one!

(Caught in Sky Lakes)

You won't believe it! I caught a fish in the forest at night that was already dead! Then it tried to eat me! I threw it away and ran! Now I want to stick it in someone's dresser to see what happens, so go fish it back up for me will ya?!

(Caught in Surface)
Oh! Thanks for the fish I asked for, now scram!
Awesome catch! It's all going according to plan! He he he!
You make a great errand monkey! Now go away!
Muahahahahaha! You did it! You're still in one piece though, how boring!
Woah!? You actually did what I asked, and survived! Nice, hand it over and beat it!
You know, super scary things lurk in the water during a Blood Moon! You should totally go try it! I'll watch from here!
You should try fishing when the water is all bloody! It's to die for!
I'm totally scared right now! It is all YOUR fault!
How can I fish out there?! Are you crazy, or just stupid!?
What, you think I like parties because I am a kid? Well, you're right, so get to partying!
Yes! It's raining! Now I can watch you get soaking wet while you fish for me!
I always go fishing in the rain! It's why I wear this hat!
Thunderstorms are the best time to go fishing! Also the most dangerous! That's why I'll send you to do it for me!
This one time at fishing camp, lightning struck the lake! Suddenly, all the fish floated up to the surface for free!
Wind is usually a great time to fish, but this is too much! I almost hooked my eye out!
Is this some kinda hurricane!? I almost got hit by a dolphin!

I hate places like this. I can't kill what's already dead!
If you see any suspicious activity out in that fog, I wasn't involved.
Parties are great for getting people to come out of their shell, just like with bullets.
Heard a rumor that some clouds are literally out to get you! Show 'em who's boss with one of my guns!
Flying fish? I call that target practice!
A lightning gun? Don't have time for that, man. I love my bullets!
If you time it right, no one will hear your gunshots with the thunder.
Was tryin' out my new gun, but the wind kept me off target!
Don't spray and pray in the wind, buddy!
Only textures of type '.png' and '.xnb' may be loaded.
Textures loaded must match the original size, got ({ActualWidth},{ActualHeight}) but expected ({NeededWidth}, {NeededHeight}).
I've got the cure for what ails ya! Get it? Ale? No?
Do you think {Steampunker} has an extra of that gun? I know a witch that may want one.
No wonder {Demolitionist} has so many accidents. You can't imagine how much ale he buys from me.
Normally, I'm not much of a fan of Goblins, but {GoblinTinkerer} seems to be an alright sort.
{?!Day}Really quiet out there. A little too quiet...
{?!Day}Check in with me, and do your job.
{?BloodMoon}You know, where I'm from, a Blood Moon is actually just an excuse to get some fresh air.
{?MoonLordDefeated}Moon Lord, don't you mean Abyss Lord?
{?HardMode}I know a Lavamancer that would really like that hellstone down in the underworld.
{?Homeless}Know any good places to set up shop? Would love to open up a bar here.
They say you're strong, well, I know strong. Let's see if you measure up.
Back where I'm from, we only serve Root Beer...
This is a big upgrade from wiping that table all day.
Life's a challenge when you're just naturally better than everyone else.
A lot of tenacity and a little bit of luck can go a long way...
Have you seen any Meburs around here?
{Dryad} seems nice. I should bring her back with me.
The first thing you need to know about are the special defensive artifacts I've got for sale, but only if you've got some Defender Medals!
If you successfully repel the invasion, you'll be awarded with more Defender Medals, which you can bring to me to purchase more artifacts and some other special rewards!
I've also heard rumors that the power of the artifacts themselves may be further unlocked if you defeat the Old One's Army. Perhaps you could even use them any time you wish!
You can use these artifacts to create traps and defensive towers. Doing so consumes Etherian mana, a special energy dropped only by members of the Old One's Army!
Challenging the Old One's Army is rather simple. They are attracted to the power of the Eternia Crystals, and that can be used to bait them out.
To place an Eternia Crystal, you must obtain an Eternia Crystal and a stand to put it in. It just so happens, you can buy em from me!
You'll want to place your Eternia Crystal stand in a pretty open, flat area. Lots of walls and stuff might make it pretty difficult to protect!
Once your stand is set up, just interact with it while holding an Eternia Crystal, and prepare for a fight!
Of course, you can't let the Old One's Army destroy the Eternia Crystal! This will have catastrophic consequences for my home world of Etheria!
You can place defenses at the cost of 10 Etherian mana. Once placed, the Eternia Crystal will release some of this mana. Otherwise, you will need to defeat enemies to get more.
With the help of the defenses, you will have to repel several waves of invaders who are attempting to destroy both you and the Eternia Crystal!
Great job on fighting off the Old One's Army! But I'm sure we haven't seen the last of them, they didn't put up much of a fight this time.
The Army of the Old One's keeps getting stronger, yet you keep pushing them back! But something tells me they aren't quite finished with us yet.
You really kept the full force of the Old One's Army at bay? Maybe you should visit Etheria some time.
We should really do something about the Old One's Army. Ask me about the Eternia Crystal if you want to learn more.
For starters, take a few of these Defender Medals, on the house! I've got some special defenses you can purchase, but only with Defender Medals!
Huh? How did I get here? The last thing I remember was a portal opening up in front of me...
Etheria has some dark places, but this takes the cake!
The bar seems kinda dead tonight. Smells like it, too!
There's a party happening here! I had just wiped down the bar, too.
You should sit down and have a little fun. Don't worry, I don't think any kobolds will crash this party.
You look like a drowned, shaggy dog! How 'bout you down some ale, eh?
Wipe your feet before you step in here, the floor was just waxed!
Take shelter from the storm! Sit down for a pint.
You look a bit frazzled! Perhaps a mug'll calm your singed nerves.
There goes the roof. I had just had it redone yesterday!
Hold onto your bonnet, there's a real breeze out today.
The most vile, stone-cold entities emerge in the blinding chaos of bone-piercing icy wind and snow. Every step is cold and dangerous.
When the moon rises drenched in blood, the dead rise with it! These macabre creatures seek to add fresh meat to their dripping ranks.
Tough monsters, abandoned cabins, and golden treasure adorn the dark, vacant caverns tunneled beneath the underground.
Winter is here! Time to celebrate with twinkling lights, ugly sweaters, and a fat old fellow wearing a bright red suit.
When the Corruption grows through the desert, vile things long since buried in the sand awaken with pure malice.
Cold ice infused with even colder Corruption results in bitterly-frozen terrors lurking beneath the treacherous icy caverns.
The Corruption's hold in the sandstone weakened the seals that held an assortment of ancient magicked beings at bay.
A hive mind of grotesque, biological infections which aim to consume all life whilst feeling absolutely nothing.
With the Crimson seeping through the sands, dark things long forgotten rise again to seek out and destroy life.
These bitterly cold caverns of ice, saturated with the blood of Crimson, host a new variety of menacing frozen fiends.
The Crimson's bloody veins broke up the tombs that once held magicked beings, which are now released to commit mayhem.
After 4:30am, the sun rises in the sky and the most dangerous of beings flee from the light. It's a great time to explore!
Endless dunes of sand reside here, scorched by the never-ending sun. Few things have adapted to survive in this environment.
Familiar creatures of horror rapidly grip the lands this day, for no mere mortal can resist the evil of the blackened sun.
This organized family of cold-hearted killers wish to ice any who cross them, and they don't like snitches... capisce?
Ho Ho Ho! On this not-so-silent night, festive beings wish to shower the world with gifts of blood and carnage.
A ragtag army of crude, barbaric goblins set out to conquer and destroy. Some wield dark, evil magic.
A glistening, dark material adorns the caverns here. Granite paves the way for progress in architectural fashion and durable monsters.
When areas of death become littered with graves, a thick mist of concentrated eeriness blankets the land.
As the Hallow responds to the encroaching evils, it inadvertently awakens things that have slept beneath the sands for centuries.
Pumpkins grow wildly across the land, and certain creatures masquerade in unusual costumes. Trick or treat!
Ice serves as a catalyst for the blessing, the Hallow's luminous source of power. Strong entities take advantage of this light.
The blessing swept through the ancient sands, awakening dangerous creatures once forgotten to time.
Thick trees, brambled vines, and relentless beasts of nature inhabit this dense canopy of lush growth, sprouted from seemingly limitless mud.
A smooth material wrought with pleasing veins of color coat the walls of this cavern. An ancient civilization of monsters dwell here.
Technologically advanced beings from another world who want to eradicate all primitive life with their superior weaponry.
The fragments left behind from plummeting meteorites burn endlessly with astrological energy, some of which appears to be alive.
A purple lunar seal protected by powerful guardians. This one representing a stormy celestial body known as 'nebula'.
After 7:30pm, the moon rises in the sky. All manner of evil things, living and dead, roam the lands in the dark.
This is no mirage! The clandestine pools of water glittering in the desert sun are the only source of life in these desolate sands.
An endless ocean stretched to the horizon awaits at the world's edge, filled with infinitely hungry creatures from the watery depths.
Minions from Etheria - they may have mistakenly invaded this world, but they wish to rule it nonetheless!
This day, for no particular reason, everyone decided to throw a party. There's always time for a celebration!
A seafaring horde of armed bandits that lust after the riches of the land, collecting treasures and taking no prisoners.
A bitter harvest rises in the dead of night. Creatures of evil and darkness spook the lands, killing everything in their path.
When it rains, it pours. Creatures which normally thrive in water may roam the land and sky. Beware the angered clouds.
The sands of the desert rage like a stormy sea, with deadly creatures swimming among them.
It is rumored that there is a land far above the clouds, where ancient treasures are guarded by powerful winged creatures.
For reasons beyond any meteorological explanation, slimy things are raining down from above by the buckets!
A persistent arctic jet stream left a part of the world permanently cold. Only the hardiest of beasts can survive this harsh region.
A red lunar seal protected by powerful guardians. This one representing a flaming celestial event known as 'solar flares'.
In this deadly place, there lurk arachnids with many legs, many eyes, and a thirst for blood. They sow thick webs threaded with malice.
A blue lunar seal protected by powerful guardians. This one representing a glittering celestial remnant known as 'stardust'.
Anywhere where one can see the trees, the mountains, and the sky. Not all creatures are powerful or even hostile.
Surface mushroom patches must be cultivated by hand, but doing so may draw attention from strong mycanoids.
A cancerous Corruption thriving off the sins of the living. Its sole desire is to consume all things, leaving behind only a lifeless void.
Constructed long ago as a once thriving city, this dark and evil place now serves as the home for its cursed former inhabitants.
A divine and overzealous force, 'The Hallow', serves as a cure to combat evil with its majestic, powerful creatures of light.
Stone-crafted with an ancient mineral alloy, this indomitable temple houses the Lihzahrd; a crude, yet advanced reptilian race.
A doomed haven of fire and brimstone - run rampant with demons and devils - offers no sanctuary for the living.
Just below the surface, there's no shortage of dirt. Basic ore, mundane treasure, and weak monsters live down there.
With the ancient spirits of light and dark released, the Corruption's reach drastically increased and its minions greatly empowered.
With the ancient spirit of darkness released, the Crimson's veiny growth reaches new depths, and its macabre fiends gain strength.
Beneath the sandy surface lies weathered, hard sandstone.  Massive nests of deadly insects and more infest these ancient burrows.
With the evils now unleashed into the depths of the world, the Hallow fights back with powerful minions of light.
The tangled world beneath the muddy jungle proves perilous to any adventurer. Within, be on guard for voracious plants and bugs.
A curious deviation of nature, large mushrooms grow densely from glowing blue grass. Tough 'mycanoids' defend the area.
Tunnels carved throughout frigid ice result in slippery pitfalls and freezing pools - all patrolled by the sub-zero denizens of the deep.
A green lunar seal protected by powerful guardians. This one representing a deep celestial void known as 'vortex'.
Don't get carried away! Nature is throwing a party and wishes to sweep everybody - and everything - off their feet!
A vision of a deadly omen wrought forth by a powerful cultist, often appears with reckless cosmic summoning of wyvern spirits.
The Angler, a rude fishing genius, sends others to find weird, rare fish. He rewards random items, entertained by any misfortunes.
Some angler fish are content to lie in wait for their prey, but these are perfectly happy to aggressively chase down an underwater meal.
When severe storms roll through, it is said that the skies are angry. This cloud in particular is especially livid!
When a Man Eater consumes enough human flesh, it undergoes a cocoon-like metamorphosis into a far deadlier form.
These crab-like creatures scuttle about in glowing mushroom fields, heavily infested by the fungal spores.
When antlions are nesting, they hide in the surface. To defend their eggs, they projectile vomit hard globs of sand at trespassers.
These enormous fish thrive in the jungle waters near veins of unstable magicks, which make them unusually strong and hostile.
Remnants of a long lost expeditionary force, these stout warriors mindlessly patrol the caves in which they died.
The most elite vikings were worthy of the strongest armor. It seems that it wasn't terribly effective, given their state now.
The Arms Dealer has everything anyone could need to shoot things dead, from little round bullets to guns made from sharks.
Clinging tightly to their parents and rarely seen, these miniature slimes will swarm anyone who harms their mother.
Found in hives and nests all throughout the jungle, these tiny pests will swarm an adventurer at every turn.
Found in hives and nests all throughout the jungle, these tiny pests will swarm an adventurer at every turn.
The Zoologist, resident lycanthrope, adores animals. Her fox-like biology resulted from a cursed animal bite.
Mimics which fall to Corruption grow larger and more powerful as a result. They can be birthed from ordinary chests by force.
Mimics which are enthralled by the Crimson are empowered dramatically. They can be birthed from ordinary chests by force.
Mimics struck with the blessing surge with energy and become powerful. They can be birthed from ordinary chests by force.
A simple white bird which enjoys a calm sunny day.
This little blue bird came looking for worms.
A rare, red-crested friend of the forest.
They have eight legs, eight eyes, and eight ways to cocoon and feast upon an unsuspecting victim.
Most spiders operate independently, but ones touched by the Crimson hive coordinate together to consume life.
A large, worm-like demon, dripping with blood - both its own, and its victim's. It's a bloody nightmare of a fiend!
Like the piranha, these swarming fish thirst for blood. Birthed from tainted blood themselves, their hunger is truly intense.
Jellyfish swimming in the bloody waters of the Crimson become infected, converting them to its all-consuming cause.
The blood-dripping organic matter in these mummies display far better preservation than the rest of their ilk.
An enormous shelled water demon which feeds off the negative energy of a Blood Moon. Brutally responds to being pestered.
Summoned in small groups by the Nautilus to aid their master in battle. Thick are the streams of blood squirted from their bodies.
With enough exposure to a Blood Moon, zombies become twisted and cursed with everflowing blood pouring out from their rotten flesh.
It's said that centuries ago, there was once a clan of ninjas that hid in the shadows of the world. It seems they are long dead now.
Mighty serpentine dragons once ruled hell, but long ago shed their obsidian scales. A skeletal husk is all that remains.
A piece of Cthulhu torn asunder, this vile mastermind pulses with agony and aids the Crimson in an attempt to avenge its master.
These Martian soldiers brandish crude laser weaponry that releases dangerous short-range radiation, hence the protective helmets.
A vibrant beetle-like bug. Fish are extremely attracted to these.
Fuzzy wuzzy creatures that prefer safe, friendly locations.
Is it a bunny in a slime costume? Or is it a slime in a bunny costume? Halloween can be very confusing sometimes.
Judging by the outfit, Santa appears to have recruited some bunnies to be his little helpers this year.
Soulless and cruel, this pig-masked psychotic killer brandishes a powerful chainsaw in which to dismember every living thing.
Beautiful fluttering insects that love sunrises. Fish are attracted to these based on their color variety.
They are small, hard to see, and swiftly flap about in unpredictable ways. They often carry diseases, such as rabies.
Once living beings infused by the blessing, they erratically make chase with an uncontrollable surge of luminous power.
A playful prank gone wrong, clowns will unleash these explosive chompers on their enemies. Also great for parties!
In the depths of the darkest corruption lies cursed-fire belching, betentacled nightmares stretching from the very walls themselves.
Once trapped under a curse, the Clothier is the master of thread. If it's fashion that's desired, he's the man! He talks in a familiar way.
His origins unknown, this creepy fiend balances himself on a ball while hurling explosive destruction at everything around him.
Found in deep, dark caverns, these large beetles are sought out for the deep, blood-red secretions stored in their scaly exoskeleton.
Bunnies are pure beings that normally resist all forms of Corruption, but will succumb under the effects of a Blood Moon.
Goldfish mutate and become violent when exposed to a Blood Moon, allowing the Corruption to take hold of them.
Like a cancer, the putrid creatures born from the Corruption mutate and grow into bigger, more deadly forms which discharge acids.
During a Blood Moon, the normally docile penguins fall under the hostile influence of the Corruption.
Steeped in the power of Corruption, these slimes can survive being cut apart into smaller pieces, unlike their untainted brethren.
This hard shelled coastal creature could snip the toes right off a man, among other things. They are not to be trifled with.
A subterranean form of crayfish which scuttles along the cavern floors, searching for prey to clip apart with its powerful pincers.
Said to have emerged from the blackest lagoons, these fish-men lash at their victims with unmatched submerged mobility.
Manipulated through the hive mind of the Crimson, Creepers serve as the brain's eyes and orbit around it for defense in numbers.
The most common horror to be born from the Crimson, it seeks to consume pure things with unrelenting hunger.
Taking on the consistency of congealed blood and flesh, Crimslimes seek out and digest more raw material for the Crimson.
Ensorcelled by the Crimson collective, this weapon moves about and chops its enemies by its own will.
Bunnies are pure beings that normally cannot be afflicted by Crimson, but will succumb under the effects of a Blood Moon.
Goldfish become grotesque, blood-sucking fiends of the Crimson when exposed to a Blood Moon.
During a Blood Moon, the normally docile penguins become infested with the contagious growth of the Crimson.
Sworn to protect the cultist's ritual, these robed archers will fight to the death defending the lunatic devotees.
A fanatical leader hell-bent on bringing about the apocalypse by reviving the great Cthulhu through behind-the-scenes scheming.
Though it is an illusion designed to distract from the true threat, this fake cultist can still use some basic offensive magic as well.
Utterly devoted, Lunatic Devotees unfailingly worship their deity, even when threatened with death. Fear only makes them worship harder.
Wyvern souls are entwined in the atmosphere of the world. Powerful magicks can summon them through the veil with physical form.
Magicked through the pure hatred of the Corruption, this weapon flails about attempting to smash anything that breathes.
Exposed to dark rituals, this skull has begun floating around on its own, chasing the living. Its touch leaves its victims defenseless.
Hardy to extremely cold temperatures, these beetles contain a desired bluish fluid which can be used to dye textiles.
The Cyborg was built with the combined efforts of the Mechanic and the Steampunker to aid in rocket science and world defense.
All this wind can make just about anyone angry. Evidently, this includes otherwise harmless dandelions and their deadly seeds.
Doomed to watch over the Dungeon, these mages teleport to confuse their prey, before striking them down with a blast of water.
The Tavern Keep once managed a bar in another universe. He's here to help stop the Old One's Army from conquering this world.
A vicious Etherian dragon who leads the minions of the Old One's Army that found their way to this world.
A small, levitating sorcerer from Etheria who wields dark magic and can even raise fresh minions for the Old One's Army.
A small, levitating sorcerer from Etheria who wields dark magic and can even raise fresh minions for the Old One's Army.
Etherian reptiles in service of the Old One's Army. Powerful beasts, they are capable of spewing deadly purple flames.
Hurling bombs with reckless abandon, these sappers serve the Old One's Army with maniacal passion.
A unique goblin species from Etheria, they are not related Terrarian goblins. The ferocious footsoldiers of the Old One's Army.
These bulky brutes are awkward and ungainly, but their javelins are still razor sharp, and their aim is deadly.
Taking the explosive approach to a whole new level, Kobold Gliders soar the skies, seeking to bring death from above.
Rigged with an explosive payload, Kobolds have no regard for safety. They eagerly blow themselves up, hoping to take their foes with them.
Lightning Bugs from Etheria aren't just named that for their pretty lights! These ones blast their foes with shocking bolts of electricity.
A tall, hulking demi-human from the Old One's Army with unfathomable strength and vitality. He carries a big stick.
A tall, hulking demi-human from the Old One's Army with unfathomable strength and vitality. He carries a big stick.
Small armies of these skeletons are summoned from the ground by Dark Mages, loyally serving their master's will.
Wither beasts emit a defense-sapping aura from the crystals on their back. While rooted in place, they heal rapidly.
Etherian Wyverns come in a variety of shapes and sizes, and behave more like bats than the majestic Wyverns of this world.
By means unknown, this silvery metamorphic sphere levitates about on its own. It moves about quickly, often producing spikes.
Hailing from a distant land, this cyclopic monstrosity lurks in cold places, wreaking havoc on those who disturb it.
Tread carefully around this dwarf. The Demolitionist is an explosive fanatic and sells dangerous things that go 'Boom!'
Demons are the infantry of the underworld. Unlike their lesser brothers, they cast shadow magic rather than hell magic.
Sentenced to an eternity of punishment for his lifelong greedy ambitions, this man has long been corrupted into a demonic state.
These large, sapphire-shelled fleas leap around incessantly. They can drain the blood content of one man within seconds.
Sturdy as a rock, these lizard-like beasts roam the desert in search of food. Their hardened bodies make them formidable threats.
Ancient magicks corrupted the minds of the once friendly desert djinns, releasing them full of hostility from their lamps.
Wandering the dark caverns below the desert dunes, ghouls are the dessicated husks of zombies preserved by the arid environment.
Ghouls twisted by the Corruption ooze a nasty green bile that ignites on contact with skin, scorching their prey with cursed flames.
Ghouls infested by the Crimson leak vile ichor from their mouths, weakening the defenses of their foes with every bite.
Ghouls cleansed by the Hallow possess a psychedelic saliva that renders their victims confused and distracted by visions and mirages.
These unnaturally large scorpions have adapted to swiftly pursuing their prey along the walls with their sharp, venomous tails.
Worm-like monstrosities are the Corruption's most favored creatures, tunneling underneath unsuspecting victims.
Exposure to the effects of ancient magicks flowing throughout the cracks of the world causes unusual rapid growths in giant worms.
This particular zombie has a knack for finding historical artifacts, but has a terrible disdain towards snakes.
A playful sea mammal whose intelligence rivals that of humanity.
Demon eyes become erratic under a Blood Moon, sometimes twisting together into a dripping cluster of cursed blood and eyeballs.
Part man, part fly, all doctor. He's brought his most volatile and dangerous chemicals, and he's buzzing to try them out.
The Dryad is the last of her kind. She is connected with nature and can analyze its purity worldwide. She sells seeds, too!
A water fowl with beautiful plumage. Swims in the purest of water, quacking happily.
A white feathered waterfowl that swims in pure water and basks in the warm sun.
An aquatic pigron mutation from the depths of the ocean who surfaces in search of a rare, savory type of worm.
The world's largest, most deadly worm. Strengthened by ancient magicks, it can devour a spicy Terrarian quicker than they realize.
A lethal sentry that stands watch over the Dungeon's gates. Those who are deemed unworthy to enter shall not pass!
Slimes in the Dungeon became powerful by feeding off the cursed energy throughout the place. They seem particularly attracted to keys.
Sometimes, highly concentrated ectoplasm gathers inside the more powerful of the cursed inhabitants of the Dungeon.
Eccentric and rather snobby to a fault, the Dye Trader has expensive tastes. He is passionate about the materials used in the dyes he sells.
Birthed from the Corruption as a being of pure malice, its sole instincts are to pursue, punish, and kill.
Conceived from the bottomless malice of the Corruption, this mighty abyssal worm tunnels wildly to devour all in its path.
These aren't your typical elven archers. Tinkering all year long, they are excited to gift you with the hottest new arrows this season.
The elves aren't just flying toy helicopters, these are fully combat ready. All that inventing finally paid off!
Should one of these luminescent beings perish in the chaos of night, a sleeping tyrant is rumored to violently awaken.
Worms infused with fallen star magic glow with a glittering light. Fish are extremely attracted to these.
Animated by the blessed light of the crystals, it will slice through anything to cleanse the world's evils.
If trees could scream, this evil evergreen would do so constantly. Deadly are the ornaments hurled from its branches.
Not the typical garden-variety bunny. This one has been tampered with, and has an explosive temper as a result.
For mysterious reasons, fish are known to mutate with other living things or even man-made objects. This one is especially violent.
A piece of Cthulhu ripped from his body centuries ago in a bloody war. It wanders the night seeking its host body... and revenge!
A powerful zombie-like creature whose eye can see for miles, and blow away opponents with powerful lasers.
It would be unwise to face off with one of these unfeeling, hungry mutations. Their mouths are large enough to devour all things.
Glowing winged humanoid creatures the size of a butterfly. Attuned to the world around them, they excel at finding shiny things.
Glowing winged humanoid creatures the size of a butterfly. Attuned to the world around them, they excel at finding shiny things.
Glowing winged humanoid creatures the size of a butterfly. Attuned to the world around them, they excel at finding shiny things.
Appears at night in calm locations, illuminating the sky with strobing green light. Fish are fairly attracted to these.
A lesser demon imbued with hell magic. Capable of teleporting and hurling phantom fireballs towards their foes.
These buoyant terrors of the darkest crimson depths most definitely, without question, are both floaty and gross.
These ferocious flakes are the frozen minions of the Ice Queen. Where this sinister snow falls, so shall her icy judgment.
Certain species of fish gain the most peculiar abilities when it rains. They only like one thing about land-dwellers: their flesh.
Kept as pets and guardians by the Lihzahrd race, the flying snakes will attack any who trespass on the Temple's protected grounds.
Built from parts of deceased Terrarians, this stout monster resulted from a crazy man's desire to create life with his own hands.
Rumors speak of a small-minded hunchback who assisted in mad science. This small fellow reacts unpredictably when approached.
Prefers bodies of water filled with thick growth. Perfectly content both on land and underwater.
Some fish exposed to glowing mushroom spores become a curious mushroom-jellyfish hybrid, glowing softly in the watery depths.
Touched by the blessing, these nocturnal slimes evolved into a levitating snail-like creature which spits powerful beams of light.
During the most harrowing times, these apparitions float aimlessly through the depths to steal the life from those they envy.
The oversized cousins of Cave Bats, these bats are more dangerous and can confuse their enemies with their bite.
No one knows where these giant skulls came from, but like their smaller cousins, they seek out and curse the living with their magic.
An oversized cousin of the bat found only in the Jungle, giant flying foxes hunt the night skies looking for prey.
To overcome their slow speed, shellies have developed the ability to hide inside their spiked shell and hurl themselves at their foes.
No one takes the giant tortoises seriously. Not until they come hurtling through the air, a spinning, spiky ball of death.
These itty bitty diggy dawgs dig through the earth and take focused spelunkers by surprise, causing unwanted distress.
Martians who show great potential in close combat are equipped with powerful energy spears that can atomize anything.
A gingerbread man seeking vengeance for his long-eaten brethren. He may look yummy, but this is one tough cookie.
A snail that has mutated to adapt to the glowing mushroom environment. Fish are significantly attracted to these.
A tiny long-bearded sneak who resides in oversized trees. Becomes a lawn ornament when exposed to sunlight.
Lending ranged support to the Goblin Army, archers keep a distance and pick off distracted and overwhelmed foes.
Common footsoldiers of the Goblin Army, these foul creatures are good for little more than cannon fodder... and breaking down doors.
The Goblin Army sends lone soldiers out from the beaches to seek out colonies to conquer. They give warning with a tattered sigil.
Half-shark, half-goblin, completely murderous! One of the numerous reasons to just stay home during a Blood Moon.
As primitive as they are, some goblins have the potential for manipulating magicked shadow energy through a form of hexing.
Gifted in the darkest of magics, she summons unfathomable shadowflame ghasts through a powerful hex.
Quick strike units of the Goblin Army, these pesky foes specialize in nimble movement and close-quarters combat.
Exiled from the rest of goblinkind for being an intelligent pacifist, the Tinkerer sells tools for combining accessories into stronger versions.
The backbone of the Goblin Army infantry, these heavily-armored soldiers can take tremendous damage as they march undeterred.
A seemingly ordinary goldfish, until it decides to rain.
A remarkable display of ingenuity constructed by the Lihzahrd clan. Powered by solar energy cells, it is ready to guard the Temple.
The Golfer is a wise, middle-aged man who sells all sorts of golfing equipment. He's got game and knows how to score.
Earth elementals manifest through many forms by taking on the properties of different materials, such as this hardy granite.
Strong are the magicked spirits which inhabit the granite masses deep below, this type in particular taking on a humanoid shape.
It leaps tall blades of grass in a single bound. Fish are fairly attracted to these.
Martians are conscripted into military service, and those who do not make the cut are sent out unarmed to distract the enemy as fodder.
An exotic waterfowl that thrives in the desert oasis.
In the ruins of an ancient civilization now deeply buried, some of its spear-hurling soldiers still walk its marble-adorned paths.
Slimy, yet satisfying! Fish are somewhat attracted to these.
The Guide always offers useful advice and crafting recipes. His origins and unusual connections to this world remain a mystery.
Beneath the Hallow's cleansing blanket lies a vengeful fae goddess bent on scrubbing the land of any and all impurity.
Winged, demi-human women defend their territory against invaders by impaling them with their razor-sharp feathers.
This menacing nightmare rides out into the night to harvest living souls on his seeing-eye horse, for he has no head of his own.
A solemn butterfly seeking blooms rooted in hell. Its wings glimmer with fiery veins.
Most certainly not a good boy, this vicious demon dog is more than eager to guide living beings to the underworld with every bite.
These hyper, demented, slug-like fiends serve the crimson horde with an unstoppable appetite for blood and flesh.
This particular pumpkin seeks revenge for being carved. His hearty leaps become quicker the more he is carved into.
As if bats weren't enough of a nuisance already, Ice Bats can freeze flesh solid with a touch, leaving their prey defenseless.
Water elementals become icy when dense strong magicks accumulate in the coldest places. Their frosty shards freeze all.
Sub-zero temperatures, blinding snow flurries, and being blasted apart by an icy construct are some of the dangers of blizzards.
If this icy towering monstrosity wishes for someone's soul, they'll surely let it go... right from their cold, dead hands.
Slimes that spent too long in arctic temperatures may begin to partially freeze, developing a shifting layer of ice on their surface.
Like their jungle cousins, ice tortoises are an unexpectedly serious threat, possessing surprising speed and mobility.
Filled to the brim with powerful ichor, these squid-like abominations spew their corrosive bio-fluid at their prey.
Mermen rarely stray far from the ocean. Those that do can become lost, wander into cold caverns, and become icy undead fish men.
Blessed with the prismatic light of the Hallow, the Illuminant Bats are a vibrant pink blur arcing across the darkness of the Underground.
Slimes exposed to the light of the Hallow's crystals begin to emit that very same light, glowing brightly in the darkness.
These small, annoying creatures aren't to be underestimated. A deadly end awaits for those swarmed by these fangy rodents.
The itsy bitsy spider climbed up a jungle vine, down came a hapless explorer and the spider got to dine. The End.
Slimes normally aren't intelligent, but occasionally they merge together to become a powerful force to swallow all things.
Every year, Krampus is tasked to punish all of the naughty children, but he's taken the day off to participate in this mayhem instead!
These scaly insects thrive in thick subterranean foliage. Their secretions stain many materials in a beautiful violet color.
A brilliant red insect often associated with luck. Fishing with these as bait may result in unwanted karma.
Freshly hatched from their eggs, larval antlions should not be underestimated. Though young, they are still very aggressive.
A variation of firefly which adapted to the intense conditions of the world's infernal core. It mimics sparking embers.
Due to the heat of the underworld, these slimes have taken on the properties of lava. Slaying them is difficult and dangerous.
A worm-like parasite spit forth from the Wall of Flesh, filled with the lifeblood of its host. This blood has healing properties.
Appears at night in blessed locations, filling the sky with flashing cyan light. Fish are especially attracted to these.
A reclusive race of reptilian folk found exclusively in the mysterious jungle Temple. They look primitive, but are quite advanced.
Naked and afraid, this girl stands still, deep in the world, as if waiting for someone to rescue her and lead her to the surface.
Representing a stormy celestial body known as 'nebula', this tower holds the seal locking away a terrifying tyrant.
Representing a flaming celestial event known as 'solar flares', this tower holds the seal locking away a terrifying tyrant.
Representing a glittering celestial remnant known as 'stardust', this tower holds the seal locking away a terrifying tyrant.
Representing a deep celestial void known as 'vortex', this tower holds the seal locking away a terrifying tyrant.
An unsavory larval bug which feasts on dead, rotting matter. Fish are somewhat attracted to these.
Wanders aimlessly to infest the living with undeath, unaware of its own maggoty infestation.
A unique species of snail which withstands extreme heat. Its boiling slime trail melts down most weaker surfaces.
A sharp-toothed plant with a taste for human flesh. It has the ability to hide inside the mud and reach over great distances.
The data collected from these drones are sent back to the motherships moments before they self-destruct onto their foes.
Martian soldiers who lack combat ability may instead be deployed for their mechanical aptitude, constructing turrets on the field.
Lacking offensive weaponry, officers in the Martian forces favor defensive measures to focus on relaying tactics to the soldiers.
Sensing growing power on the planet, otherworldly beings send space-age technology to scan for advanced lifeforms.
An advanced flying saucer from somewhere well beyond this world. The destruction from its weaponry is unimaginable.
Named after a historic Terrarian, these turrets are built by Martian engineers and rain devastating energy upon anyone nearby.
A wonder of Martian technology constructed from the strongest metals and infused with biological components.
The Mechanic was imprisoned for her aptitude in engineering. She sells wiring and tools for putting together anything imaginable.
An ancient monster with a petrifying gaze. The snakes which grow from her scalp like hair grant her these powers.
The Merchant acts as a simple general store of sorts, providing useful starter tools and supplies needed for exploration.
When meteorites strike the surface, their fragments lay scattered for the taking. Some pieces are alive, and will attack.
This stone-cold, yet maniacal gangster never snuffs the celebrating do-gooders without bringing along his 'Lil' Pokey'.
The mastermind behind all terrors which befall the world, freed from his lunar prison. Practically a god, his power knows no limits.
The empowered flora of the Jungle has merged with these species of Hornet, strengthening their exoskeletons and stingers.
Rarely, exposure to jungle toxins causes certain moths to mutate to enormous size. They release a valuable dust on death.
Critical to the lifecycle of the slime species, these oversized jiggling masses are often found carrying their young deep underground.
A behemoth of an insect attracted to the eerie anti-glow of a solar eclipse. With a rapid gestation period, it multiplies quickly.
The creatures which burst from the eggs laid by mothron can be as deadly and as relentless as their daunting mothers.
These enormous murder trees nightmarishly stomp about, prepared to shower endless fiery destruction upon all life.
Mice squeak around harmlessly, looking for small insects in damp underground locations.
This aggressive species of ladybug is quite at home near glowing mushrooms, living symbiotically with the fungus.
An intelligent being who seeks out souls to steal, utilizing nails from his own body both as a weapon and as defensive measures.
Celestial power fuels the aggression of these violent beasts, allowing them to run down those who trespass the pillar's area.
These brain-like celestial beings have psionic capabilities, phasing through space and summoning powerful optical minions.
These psionic, squid-like beasts levitate with celestial energy and latch onto the head of their prey, disrupting brain functions.
The cosmic power held by these humanoid warriors grant them psychic abilities, in which they use to accurately shoot down foes.
The Nurse's snarky attitude and poor bedside manner may be scary, but for a price, she will cure all that ails a wounded Terrarian.
Bringing his massive chompers to bear, the Nutcracker frolics through the wintery night. Nuts aren't the only thing he can crack.
Masterfully deceives explorers by posing as a lost girl, then attacks with ferocious might, blood-lust in her eyes.
This hapless Old Man carries the burden of a heavy curse. It's said at night he transforms into a horrific demon which guards the Dungeon.
A large, wise predatory bird which hunts nocturnally from the tree tops.
The Painter can talk about all the different shades of colors with which one can paint the walls. He'll sell but a handful of them!
In distant history, these mighty undead knights once guarded a prosperous city before a massive curse befell them.
A pirate's best friend, the parrot, will tear the eyes out of any greasy landlubber with its sharp, pointy talons.
Someone put a party hat on a bunny. It must be a real party animal.
Positive beyond comprehension, the Party Girl will use any excuse to celebrate. She sells party favors and flashy things.
The smallest slime ever recorded, their extreme cellular density makes them incredibly durable for their small size. They eat money.
Just one of these sharp-toothed fish can easily end a life. Luckily, they tend to swarm their victims in large groups! Life is grand.
Ahoy! The only good Pirate Captain is... one that sells cannons and weapons to take out all competing Pirate Captains!
A pirate captain's love for riches is only rivaled by his obsession with heavy gunpowder and large, rampart-shattering cannons!
Once mercenaries from a distant land, Corsairs brandish deadly scimitars with unyielding skill and a cut-throat agenda.
Some wee lasses aren't content staying at port waiting for their men to return from a raid, so they join in on the deadly fun!
Nobody knows if 'Dead Eye' refers to their precise aim, or the fact that one of their eyes is indeed 'dead'... like their targets.
They are either washing the deck of their ship of seaweed and ale, or wiping the dirt with the faces of unsuspecting Terrarians.
When the pirates face strong opposition in their pillaging raids, they bring their majestic floating galleon as backup. Cannons away!
A larger, more luminous form of fairy. Pixies provide the Hallow with more blessed light and aid in the cleansing of the land.
A dormant, yet powerful floral guardian awoken by the fallout of Cthulhu's destroyed machinations. Its reach spans the entire jungle.
The intense hateful energies emanating from these spirits grant them the ability to move objects, truly for the purpose of killing.
Whatever possessed this suit of armor to suddenly walk about and start killing everyone? It lacks a corporeal body.
Surprise! The most unexpected gift this holiday season, the Present Mimic is a nicely gift-wrapped box of teeth and death.
Shy and innocent, this happy young lady sees the positive in everything, and everybody. She appreciates all of her subjects, from all walks of life.
A singular probe detached from the Destroyer's body serves as a remote laser battery, often in a swarm of other probes.
This masked killer's quiet demeanor and cunning ability to hunt allows him to ambush his victims without being detected.
A pumpkin has many faces. A pumpkin will murder all with many sharp blades. A pumpkin is king of the harvest.
These fish prefer isolated, extreme climates where competition is scarce, such as the lakebeds of a desert oasis.
This highly aggressive monstrosity responds violently when her larva is disturbed; the honey-laden hives are her home turf.
Hallowed slimes consolidated into a haughty, crushing force adorned in dazzling crystals. She is rumored to grow wings.
The blue-spectrumed crystal slimes specialize in growing and ejecting pointed crystal shards from their gelatinous bodies.
On the pink side of the crystal spectrum, these crystal slimes pop off tumor-like gel growths to assault their enemies.
Crystal slimes on the purple spectrum grow wings much like their royal creator, becoming aerial threats.
These blessing-infused gelatin menaces glow vibrantly in a rainbow of hues. As a result, they require a constant liquid intake.
These fuzzy rodents sniff about in putrid locations scavenging for food. They are avoided in fear of diseases they may carry.
Nevermore. Nevermore. Nevermore. Nevermore. Nevermore. Nevermore. Nevermore. Nevermore.
The elite specialists in the Martian Invasion Force are equipped with more precise and deadly laser rifles; effectively snipers.
The reaper's list stretches endlessly with the names of those who will soon depart this world. His sickle will make sure of that.
Conjuring potent spears of dark magic, these elite demons are a serious threat to any who dare enter their abode.
Belonging to a pair of mechanically recreated Eyes of Cthulhu, this one focuses its energy into firing powerful lasers.
Dense-minded living stone formation. Awaits weary cavern dwellers to pound them into juicy rubble.
Tim's more powerful and much better-looking older brother. He, too, prefers the heat, but not excessively.
An unusual amphibious bipedal lizard which inhabits the dark caverns. When threatened, it spews a highly corrosive acid everywhere.
The most intense sandstorms draw forth powerful earth elementals. With this feminine form, her tornadoes tear all asunder.
Deserts are very dry, but the Sand Slime seems to have successfully adapted to the harsh conditions by becoming a pile of living sand.
Only present during a specific time of year, Santa Claus makes a big entrance and an even bigger, rather explosive exit. Ho! Ho! Ho!
This jolly bad boy wants to stuff everyone's stockings with the gift of their entrails. This cranky Kringle's gone postal.
Harmlessly scuttles around the desert looking for food. Fish are barely attracted to these.
Despite its menacing appearance, it is quite docile unless threatened or facing smaller prey. Fish are occasionally attracted to these.
Native to the Martian homeworld, these creatures function similarly to horses. That is, if horses could fire lasers from their eyes.
Elite Ray Gunners often ride these powerful alien creatures into battle as cavalry. If their mount dies, they will pursue on foot.
A larger bird that inhabits coastal areas. Watch out for droppings!
A gentle critter which swims harmlessly in the ocean depths.
This unusually large snail makes its home deep in the ocean. Its mucus can be manufactured into a purple dye.
A soft-shelled reptile that prefers saltwater and marine prey.
Ancient magicks have unleashed the dark influences that gave birth to the Eater of Worlds, producing smaller, but just as deadly worms.
Young Demon Eyes newly birthed from the Eye of Cthulhu, brought forth to protect their master by any means necessary.
The shadowflame magicks are powerful spiritual remnants of twisted goblin ancestors, wrought from powerful summoning.
Once these ocean predators catch a whiff of blood, they become relentless and unstoppable in their ravenous pursuit.
Duke Fishron's nature as a form of chimera causes his offspring to emerge more shark-like, which he uses as minions in battle.
Skeleton Archers have a keen eye, despite the general lack of eyes. Distance offers little protection from their blazing arrows.
Rocket-powered and fueled with rage, these cursed skeletons prefer the nuclear option. Part of an elite military unit in their past lives.
Most skeletons are out for blood, but not the Skeleton Merchant. He just wants to sell supplies, such as rare torches and yo-yo gear.
These eagle-eyed sharpshooters let nothing escape their crosshairs. Part of an elite military unit in their past lives.
The disembodied bones of a former tyrant pulsed with a hatred so strong, it left behind a mighty curse which guards the Dungeon.
Mechanically reconstructed for reviving Cthulhu, this Skeletron has more arms than ever before, and a variety of fierce weapons.
Sometimes, a slime's victim will turn into a zombie mid-digestion. Walking around like that is quite awkward for both parties.
The still-animate severed pieces of an injured Corrupt Slime, Slimelings can still put up a fight, and have strength in numbers.
Is it a slime in a bunny costume? Or is it a bunny in a slime costume? Halloween can be very confusing sometimes.
The Slimer has become airborne with wings of unknown origin. The wings are easily knocked off with force, depriving it of its flight.
Slow and covered in a slick mucus. Fish are especially attracted to these.
A slimy mollusk that thrives in damp, dark places. Fish are barely attracted to these.
A sharp-toothed plant with a taste for human flesh. It has the ability to hide inside the mud and reach over great distances.
Nobody underestimates the throwing arm on this disturbed member of the snowman mafioso. He's a real slugger!
A strange, round furry mammal with an unusually large, protruding nose. They are extremely lightweight.
While the world's inhabitants celebrate festivities, gangster snowmen party by slaying everyone with their tommy guns.
Resembling a large, sentient meteorite, Corites are infused with celestial energy and will charge at anything that moves.
Wrapped in celestial energy, this worm-like creature seems invincible. Having no eyes, it seeks vibrations throughout the air.
These celestial beasts harness the power of the sun, releasing violent flares towards any intruders nearing the pillar.
Many drakanians ride the beastly Drakomires as a form of battle steed. Should the Drakomire be slain, they will pursue on foot.
These acrobatic celestial warriors can deflect incoming threats whilst spinning with their solar-infused blades.
These highly aggressive celestial soldiers carry a large, fiery spear that can melt nearly anything it penetrates.
These humanoid celestial monsters assault their foes by rolling up into a ball and charging them with their sharp, fiery spikes.
Belonging to a pair of mechanically recreated Eyes of Cthulhu, this one chases at high speed, exhaling cursed flames.
This Ice Slime has large ice shards in its mass from excessive exposure to the cold. Somehow, it is able to launch these at its prey.
Frequent consumption of the Jungle's toxins and thorns has resulted in a slime covered in venomous spikes.
Mourning Woods reproduce by snapping cuttings from their bodies and thrusting them into the soil. Splinterlings are the result.
The tables have turned on a variety of rabid bats, themselves enwrought with a deadly fungal infection.
Skeletons meandering through more moist caverns become hosts for glowing fungal growth, greatly empowering them.
A betentacled marine creature which discharges a thick, black ink when threatened. The ink is collected for aesthetic purposes.
Fast moving and erratic woodland creatures with grayish-brown fur. Got nuts?
Rare, red-furred hyperactive rodents which scurry about the woods.
A biological single-celled organism that divides and multiplies rapidly with the limitless power of celestial energy.
A biological single-celled organism that divides and multiplies rapidly with the limitless power of celestial energy.
A cosmic jellyfish-type creature infused with abundant celestial energies which summons smaller minions to serve as its weaponry.
This slow-moving celestial soldier fires cosmic rays at unsuspecting invaders, defending the pillar without hesitation.
This beastly celestial arachnid rapidly spawns swift and relentless offspring to distract its prey as it prepares to devour them.
The celestial energies of which this worm is born give its body and tail near unstoppable power as it twists through the skies.
The Steampunker has a particular taste for steam-fueled machinery and gadgets. She sells her gizmos with an endearing accent.
The Stylist loves style, gossip, and hair. Aside from performing a miracle makeover, she sells some hair product as well.
Creeping from the depths of the darkest swamps, this algae-dripped beast desires to drown away anyone in his path.
With thick armor and mighty boomsticks, it's clear these bones are prepared for a siege. Part of an elite military unit in their past lives.
This grumpy Tax Collector has literally been to hell and back. Greedy to a fault, he's truly only concerned with money.
It's uncertain if the bride was wed before or after her death, but the story ends tragically for anyone who crosses her path.
A mechanical simulacrum of Cthulhu's spine decorated in laser-armed probes, which detach from its body when damaged.
Tall, handsome, and dead. This unlucky fellow did not survive his wedding and is ready to take it out on everyone.
The Wall of Flesh's many mouths, attached by bloody veins. As a last resort, they can tear away and hungrily chase down threats.
The Wall of Flesh's many mouths, attached by bloody veins. As a last resort, they can tear away and hungrily chase down threats.
A Terrarian girl possessed by the most evil of spirits, she gains superhuman abilities and behaves both arbitrarily and violently.
An enchanter in life, this funny fellow won't give up his robe or wizard hat without a fight. He prefers warmer caverns.
The desert is home to one of the largest varieties of worms across the land. It has a voracious appetite for careless explorers.
An unseen deity responsible for a torch's eternal flicker, however easily angered by the unsightly, ungrateful abuse of torch placement.
In life, this torch-wielding zombie joined an angry mob to hunt the undead. In death, it joined an undead mob to hunt the living.
Guaranteed to keep the vegetable supplies in check. Might possibly become a hat.
Lazy, devious, might bring presents. Presents might have once been breathing.
A loyal companion to many. Excitable and always ready for action.
Distantly related to the common slime, the Toxic Sludge takes down its prey with potent toxins and a disarmingly toothy smile.
The flamboyantly-dressed Traveling Merchant travels far and wide to bring unique, cultural wares from time to time.
Harnessing the hidden power of the glowing mushroom, the Truffle forges weapons and tools exclusively in his mushroom home.
An extremely rare, difficult to catch glowworm. A specific, powerful sea creature is insatiably attracted to these.
Powerful winds have blown this tumbleweed around the desert, and it is none too pleased. They roll faster with the wind than against it.
These slow, stoic creatures travel between lakes and dry land, carrying a hard shell on their backs for protection.
Their hard shells camouflage them from vicious predators by blending in with the thick, jungly environment in which they reside.
The previous owner of this umbrella learned the hard way: umbrellas are good protection against rain, but not against slime.
There's evidence of spelunkers having explored the caverns in the past... as well as evidence of them having died doing so.
Long before there were pirates, stories tell of powerful vikings who raged the seas. Their remains roam the icy caverns below.
These majestic single-horned equines storm angrily through the hallowed land in search of lowly intrusions needing to be cleansed away.
Whether he is a man who turns into a bat, or a bat who turns into a man, one thing is for sure: he's out for blood!
Higher ranking demons can possess a voodoo doll of the chosen one, whose soul is linked with the world's guardian himself.
These flying insectoids utilize wormholes to ambush intruders near the celestial pillars. They hunt in pairs and may swiftly evolve.
The final evolutionary stage of the alien hornet. They fire powerful disruptive energy at their prey, and give birth to many larvae.
The larval stage of the alien hornets. They may seem weak and harmless, but if ignored they will evolve into powerful beings.
These alien soldiers carry a versatile arsenal of celestial rifles and cosmic accessories that allow them to defy gravity.
The cosmic energy surging through these warriors builds up until their untimely demise, resulting in an explosion of lightning.
Built to survive the desert heat, avian scavengers such as these will peck apart those who come near their carrion.
They have eight legs, eight eyes, and eight ways to cocoon and feast upon an unsuspecting victim.
Serving as the world's core and guardian, the towering demon lord exists to keep powerful ancient spirits sealed away.
Glides elegantly along the surface of calm bodies of water searching for smaller bugs. Fish are occasionally attracted to these.
Cursed by the moonlight, these menacing lupines were once human. Now, they feast on their loved ones instinctively.
Some enterprising slimes ride wind currents with balloons in an effort to find food. Pop their balloons to bring them back down to earth.
It's unusual for a Lihzahrd to be outside the Temple. Even more unusual are the voodoo things he sells. He prefers his jungle digs.
The Wizard is an absent-minded, demented old man who dabbles in the arcane arts. He sells magical trinkets to train new apprentices.
Living in the harshest of climates, these savage lupines hunt in the dark of night desperately for sustenance.
A slick, tubular invertebrate found hiding in rocks, dirt, and grass. Loves the rain. Fish are especially attracted to these.
Souls belonging to the darkest of hearts were once sealed in the world's core. Now, they roam the night to add to their kind.
A colossal dragon-like creature unleashed along with the ancient spirits. It rules the skies with its unrivaled might.
An ill-tempered ape from cold, snowy regions to the north. They do not appreciate festivity, so they've come to spoil all the fun.
Zombies found in snow biomes are often found bundled up in winter clothing. It doesn't help them any, they are still dead cold!
Mermen may be rare and exotic demi-humans, but they can still die... and still come back from that a changed merman.
Some zombies never leave home without their trusty raincoat. Comfy and dry, they pursue human flesh no matter the weather.

I collected critters like you once, then I took a cursed fox bite to the knee!
Wow, like, I've never seen a full moon. For some reason, it's like I pass out every time one's around!
I have noooo idea how I got here, but it's mega rad.
{?Eclipse}Like wow, I feel like I belong with the creepy killer things running around right now. So glad I'm not that mindless.
I may not know, like, a whole lot...but I can talk your head off about nature and critters and animals and wildlife and...
My older bro calls me a lycanthrope. It means I'm like, part animal or something. He'd know, though, because he spends all his time outside!
I love animals, like, a lot! I tried to pet this weird looking fox one time, he sooo bit me, and now I became like one! Rad!
Staahp pulling on my tail, bro, it's totally real, and like...totally hurts when you pull on it!
Huh?! No, {Stylist} didn't dye my hair. It's naturally this color! It was like, dark brown before I was bitten, though!
Oh, THESE ears? Haha, totes better to hear you with, my dear!
This one time, at critter camp, I woke up one morning and everything was torn apart! Like, wow, how did I sleep through THAT?!
My instincts are totally going wild. I really need to get out of here!
Ok, like, this place is totally freaky. It makes my fur stand on end!
So, uh, I can't wear the hat. Sorry. I'm still here for the party, no worries!
Staaaap! Ugh! Not you, this lame rain.
For real!? I can't STAND being wet! It's gross.
Eek!! You have NO idea how much thunder hurts my sensitive ears.
Is it over yet? I have this, like, irrational fear of thunderstorms.
Running in the wind makes me feel so free and wild. Totes try it sometime!
The breeze blows through my hair, it's, like, woah.
